==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tipcat
<hw>Tip"cat`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A game in which a
small piece of wood pointed at both ends, called a <xex>cat</xex>, is
tipped, or struck with a stick or bat, so as to fly into the
air.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In the middle of a game at <qex>tipcat</qex>, he paused, and stood
staring wildly upward with his stick in his hand.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tipper</ent>⟦br⟧
